# Email Phishing Detection — Excel Project

This project demonstrates how phishing attempts can be identified using simple rule-based detection techniques in Microsoft Excel.

--- 
 
## Objective 

- Identify suspicious or phishing emails using:
- Domain analysis
- Urgent keyword detection
- Link presence
- Attachment checks
- Risk scoring
- Conditional formatting
- PivotTables & dashboards 

---

## Techniques Used
 
- Data cleaning
- Phishing indicator creation (domain, keywords, links, attachments)
- Weighted Risk Scoring
- Conditional formatting for high-risk emails
- Pivot-based summary
- Dashboard creation 

---

##Key Insights

- 3 high-risk emails detected
- Suspicious domains (e.g., amaz0n-support.com, micros0ft-check.com) observed
- Urgent keywords such as "urgent", "verify", "action required" flagged
- Majority of emails were safe, but several required further investigation 

